The cleric and wizard pets (do wizards still have those?) are nothing more than animated DoTs that do melee damage.   <IMG SRC="tongue.gif" border="0"><P>The best shadowknight pet does more melee damage than the best shaman pet, though the shaman pet has more HP IIRC.<P>The druid pet is the cutest, if that matters.   <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>--------------------<P>"...you've been given the reason which can distinguish between good and evil, and you've been also given free will; this may meet with difficulties at first, but it wins everything in the end, if it's fed with virtue..." – Dante Alighieri, <I>The Divine Comedy: Purgatorio</I>, XVI, 73-78
