<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
It's not so much the pet you should worry about its the way clases interact with a pet.  To a mage and enchanter a pet is a root (unless its a charmed pet then its a big bad ass mofo you best get away from).  To a necro, shaman, druid, or shadowknight a pet is a dot.  To a beastlord a pet is your best friend and you play cleric to it (or joust, no time for beastlord strategy talk).  To a wizard his familiars are just buffs.  And to both clerics and wizards their pets are wasted slots in a spellbook   <IMG SRC="biggrin.gif" border="0"> .<P>From a pure damage/hp's perspective enchanters can potentially have the best pets through charm, but since you are multiboxing and charming mobs and whatnot isn't particularly easy (at least thats the impression i got) you may want to go with a mage whose pet is the best damage dealer and has the most hp's.
</FONT>
