<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Mages have the most versatile pets.<P>I THINK Emmisary of Thule is better than the mage epic, in pure damage. Certainally not versatility, though.<P>I haven't had any experience with Beastlords. That's right, after seven months, I still haven't grouped with one. I think they come in third, though, because without lots of buffing, their pets are dopey little kittens / lizards / puppies.<P>Enchanter and Shaman pets are about equal. The enchanter pet does more damage because it can hold weapons and dual weild, the shaman pet is controllable and has a lot more hit points.<P>The shadow Knight's pet is... silly. I never use mine unless I've picked up a nice weapon that will never sell, such as a giant militia longsword, crystal fiber, or the like. Then it becomes a rather nice asset, a dot that averages about 12 damage a tick against what I'm fighting. As for losing taunt, I've noticed this fighting the Ry'Gorr Oracles in CC... they'll cast at anyone in range now, most often the pet. Also, they seem to behave as if they'rerooted. I could dot the crap out of it, melee it down to half and back off, and it'd just turn to my pet instead of chasing me. Interesting.<P>Cleric pets? Psssht, they get the best pets - every character with more than 2k HP is a cleric pet.
</FONT>
